{"title_page": "510", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2011}}\n{{Year dab|510}}\n{{for|the U.S. area code|Area code 510}}\n{{unreferenced|date=October 2017}}\n{{Year nav|510}}\n{{M1 year in topic}}\n[[File:Britonia6hcentury.png|thumb|259px|Map of [[Britons (historical)|British]] settlements (6th century)]] \n__NOTOC__\nYear '''510''' ('''[[Roman numerals|DX]]''') was a [[common year starting on Friday]] (link will display the full calendar) of the [[Julian calendar]]. At the time, it was known as the '''Year of the Consulship of Severinus without colleague''' (or, less frequently, '''year 1263 ''[[Ab urbe condita]]'''''). The denomination 510 for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the [[Anno Domini]] [[calendar era]] became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.\n\n== Events ==\n<onlyinclude>\n\n=== By place ===\n\n==== Britannia ====\n* [[Geraint son of Erbin|Battle of Llongborth]] (possibly [[Langport]] or [[Portsmouth]]): King [[Budic II of Brittany|Budic II]] of [[History of Brittany|Brittany]] seeks, after the battle, refuge at the court of [[Aergol Lawhir]], in [[Dyfed]] ([[Wales]]).\n\n==== Europe ====\n* King [[Theodoric the Great]] razes the [[Franks|Frankish]] siege at [[Arles]]; the city is heroically defended by its inhabitants, assisted by the Ostrogothic general [[Theudis]]. The [[Ostrogoths]] overrun [[Provence]] (Southern [[Gaul]]), and consolidate their gains in the region.  \n* Theodoric the Great appoints his friend [[Boethius|Anicius Manlius Severinus Boethius]], Roman [[philosopher]], to the rank of [[consul]] of the [[Ostrogothic Kingdom]]. \n\n==== Persian Empire ====\n* The [[Sasanian Empire|Sasanian Persians]] conquer the independent kingdom of [[Caucasian Albania]], a state converted to [[Christianity]] in the [[4th century]] by Armenian [[Missionary|missionaries]] (approximate date).\n</onlyinclude>\n\n== Births ==\n* [[Aredius]], [[abbot]] and [[saint]] (approximate date)\n* [[Gildas]], [[Celtic Christianity|Celtic monk]] (approximate date)\n* [[Emperor Xiaoming of Northern Wei|Xiao Ming Di]], emperor of [[Northern Wei]] (d. [[528]])\n* [[Emperor Xiaowu of Northern Wei|Xiao Wu Di]], emperor of Northern Wei (d. [[535]])\n* [[Empress Yifu|Yifu]], empress of [[Western Wei]] (d. [[540]])\n\n== Deaths ==\n* [[January 1]] &ndash; [[Eugendus]], abbot of [[Condat Abbey]] \n* [[Drest Gurthinmoch|Drest II]], king of the [[Picts]] (approximate date)\n* [[Hashim]], great-grandfather of [[Muhammad]] (approximate date)\n* [[Tato]], king of the [[Lombards]] (approximate date)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:510}}\n[[Category:510| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2011}}\n{{Year dab|510}}\n{{for|the U.S. area code|Area code 510}}\n{{unreferenced|date=October 2017}}\n{{Year nav|510}}\n{{M1 year in topic}}\n[[File:Britonia6hcentury.png|thumb|259px|Map of [[Britons (historical)|British]] settlements (6th century)]] \n__NOTOC__\nYear '''510''' ('''[[Roman numerals|DX]]''') was a [[common year starting on Friday]] (link will display the full calendar) of the [[Julian calendar]]. At the time, it was known as the '''Year of the Consulship of Severinus without colleague''' (or, less frequently, '''year 1263 ''[[Ab urbe condita]]'''''). The denomination 510 for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the [[Anno Domini]] [[calendar era]] became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.\n\n== Events ==\n<onlyinclude>\n\n=== By place ===\n\n==== Britannia ====\n* [[Geraint son of Erbin|Battle of Llongborth]] (possibly [[Langport]] or [[Portsmouth]]): [[Budic II of Brittany|Budic II]], king of [[History of Brittany|Brittany]] seeks, after the battle, refuge at the court of [[Aergol Lawhir]] in [[Dyfed]] ([[Wales]]).\n\n==== Europe ====\n* King [[Theodoric the Great]] razes the [[Franks|Frankish]] siege at [[Arles]]; the city is heroically defended by its inhabitants, assisted by the Ostrogothic general [[Theudis]]. The [[Ostrogoths]] overrun [[Provence]] (Southern [[Gaul]]) and consolidate their gains in the region.  \n* Theodoric the Great appoints his friend [[Boethius|Anicius Manlius Severinus Boethius]], Roman [[philosopher]], to the rank of [[consul]] of the [[Ostrogothic Kingdom]]. \n\n==== Persian Empire ====\n* The [[Sasanian Empire|Sasanian Persians]] conquer the independent kingdom of [[Caucasian Albania]], a state converted to [[Christianity]] in the [[4th century]] by Armenian [[Missionary|missionaries]] (approximate date).\n</onlyinclude>\n\n== Births ==\n* [[Aredius]], [[abbot]] and [[saint]] (approximate date)\n* [[Gildas]], [[Celtic Christianity|Celtic monk]] (approximate date)\n* [[Emperor Xiaoming of Northern Wei|Xiao Ming Di]], emperor of [[Northern Wei]] (d. [[528]])\n* [[Emperor Xiaowu of Northern Wei|Xiao Wu Di]], emperor of Northern Wei (d. [[535]])\n* [[Empress Yifu|Yifu]], empress of [[Western Wei]] (d. [[540]])\n\n== Deaths ==\n* [[January 1]] &ndash; [[Eugendus]], abbot of [[Condat Abbey]] \n* [[Drest Gurthinmoch|Drest II]], king of the [[Picts]] (approximate date)\n* [[Hashim]], great-grandfather of [[Muhammad]] (approximate date)\n* [[Tato]], king of the [[Lombards]] (approximate date)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:510}}\n[[Category:510| ]]\n", "name_user": "Histrydude", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/510"}
