{"title_page": "John Forgeham", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=November 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name                      = John Forgeham\n| image                     = \n| image_size                = \n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_name                = John Henry George Forgeham\n| birth_date                = 14 May 1941\n| birth_place               = [[Kidderminster]], Worcestershire, England\n| death_date                = {{death date and age|df=y|2017|3|10|1941|5|14}}\n| death_place               = [[Worthing]], West Sussex, England\n| nationality                 = British\n| occupation                = Actor\n| years_active              = 1963\u20132012\n| spouse                    = [[Georgina Hale]] (actress/divorced)<ref name=\"auto\">The People.co.uk</ref><br/>Fiesta mei Ling (actress/divorced)<ref name=\"auto\"/><br/>Arlene Garciano (2004\u20132006)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.co.uk/news/tm_objectid=16721296&method=full&siteid=93463&headline=exclusive--on-me-web-cam--son--name_page.html |title=Sunday People \u2013 News, views, gossip, pictures, video |publisher=People.co.uk |accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref>\n| children                  = 2\n}}\n\n'''John Henry George Forgeham''' (14 May 1941 \u2013 10 March 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/italian-job-john-forgeham-dead-10006919|title=The Italian Job and Footballers' Wives actor John Forgeham dies aged 75|last1=Das|first1=Shanti|last2=Saunders|first2=Emmeline|date=11 March 2017|newspaper=Daily Mirror|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>) was an English actor known for his television work, notably the role of businessman Frank Laslett in the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] series ''[[Footballers' Wives]]''.<ref>Footballers' Wives interview</ref>\n\nBorn in [[Kidderminster]], Worcestershire, Forgeham moved to [[Erdington]], Birmingham as a child,<ref name=guardian>[https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/mar/13/john-forgeham-obituary John Forgeham obituary] ''[[The Guardian]]'', 13 March 2017. Retrieved 13 March 2017.</ref> and trained at the [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]] (RADA) on a two-year scholarship (1962\u201364) and graduated with a RADA Silver medal for Best Performance student.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/john-forgeham-actor-dies-after-falling-out-of-bed-the-italian-job-footballers-wives-worthing-a7625036.html|title=Actor John Forgeham, who starred in The Italian Job, dies after falling out of bed|date=11 March 2017}}</ref> He was a member of the [[Royal Shakespeare Company]] (RSC) (from 1966 until 1972) and toured with the company both nationally and internationally. Whilst on tour in Australia he decided to stay longer than anticipated and founded the Globe Shakespeare Theatre in Sydney.<ref name=guardian/>\n\nHis many TV credits include: ''[[The Avengers (TV series)|The Avengers]]'', ''[[Z-Cars]]'', ''[[The Stone Tape]]'', ''[[Crossroads (UK TV series)|Crossroads]]'' (as [[Jim Baines]]) ''[[The Sweeney]]'', ''[[Ivanhoe (1982 film)|Ivanhoe]]'', ''[[Beau Geste (TV series)|Beau Geste]]'', ''[[Minder (TV series)|Minder]]'', ''[[The Professionals (TV series)|The Professionals]]'', ''[[Shoestring (TV series)|Shoestring]]'', ''[[Juliet Bravo]]'', ''[[C.A.T.S. Eyes]]'', ''[[Lovejoy]]'', ''[[Bergerac (TV series)|Bergerac]]'', ''[[The Governor (UK TV series)|The Governor]]'', ''Pulaski'', ''[[Making Out (TV series)|Making Out]]'', [[Nice Work (TV Drama)|''Nice Work'']], ''[[Prime Suspect]]'', ''[[London's Burning (TV series)|London's Burning]]'', ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'', ''[[The Bill]]'' and ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aveleyman.com/ActorCredit.aspx?ActorID=5898|title=John Forgeham|publisher=aveleyman.com}}</ref>\n\nFilm appearances include: ''[[The Italian Job]]'' (1969), ''[[Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall (film)|Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall]]'' (1973), ''[[Spy Story (film)|Spy Story]]'' (1976), ''[[Sheena (film)|Sheena]]'' (1984), ''[[Pope John Paul II (film)|Pope John Paul II]]'' (1984), ''The Laughter of God'' (1990), ''[[King of the Wind (film)|King of the Wind]]'' (1990), ''[[The Young Americans (film)|The Young Americans]]'' (1993), ''[[Staggered (film)|Staggered]]'' (1994), ''The Road to Ithaca'' (1999), ''[[Kiss of the Dragon]]'' (2001), [[Mean Machine (film)|''Mean Machine'']] (2001), ''[[Pledge of Allegiance (film)|Pledge of Allegiance]]'' (2007), ''[[Torture Room]]'' (2007) and ''[[Dead Man Running]]'' (2009).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2ba2927c21|title=John Forgeham}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004 he appeared in the second series of the ITV weight loss show, ''[[Celebrity Fit Club]].'' He replaced [[Freddie Starr]] as team captain, but was demoted five weeks later, the role being taken by [[James Whitaker (journalist)|James Whitaker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2b8a2a2002|title=Celebrity Fit Club[13/01/2004] (2004)}}</ref>\n\nForgeham died suddenly from [[internal bleeding]] after breaking a [[collarbone]] after falling out of bed at his home in [[Worthing]], West Sussex on 10 March 2017, aged 75.<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/john-forgeham-actor-dies-after-falling-out-of-bed-the-italian-job-footballers-wives-worthing-a7625036.html</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''The Partner'' (1963) \u2013 Adrian Marlowe\n*''[[The Italian Job]]'' (1969) \u2013 Frank\n*''[[Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall (film)|Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall]]'' (1973) \u2013 Wally\n*''[[One Hour to Zero]]'' (1976) \u2013 Sam Rogers\n*''[[Spy Story (film)|Spy Story]]'' (1976) \u2013 Security Guard\n*''[[Star Wars (film)|Star Wars]]'' (1977) \u2013 Captain Bolvan (Imperial Officer) (uncredited)\n*''[[Pope John Paul II (film)|Pope John Paul II]]'' (1984) \u2013 Officer Moljek\n*''[[Sheena (film)|Sheena]]'' (1984) \u2013 Jorgensen\n*''[[The Inquiry (1986 film)|The Inquiry]]'' (1986) \u2013 Marco\n*''[[King of the Wind (film)|King of the Wind]]'' (1990) \u2013 Blacksmith\n*''[[The Young Americans (film)|The Young Americans]]'' (1993) \u2013 Detective Gray\n*''[[Staggered (film)|Staggered]]'' (1994) \u2013 Inspector Lubbock\n*''[[Remember Me? (film)|Remember Me?]]'' (1997) \u2013 Police inspector\n*''The Road to Ithaca'' (1999) \u2013 Kemal Ahmed\n*''[[Kiss of the Dragon]]'' (2001) \u2013 Max\n*''[[Mean Machine (film)|Mean Machine]]'' (2001) \u2013 Charlie Sykes\n*''[[Pledge of Allegiance (film)|Pledge of Allegiance]]'' (2007) \u2013 Mr. Green\n*''[[Dead Man Running]]'' (2009) \u2013 Terry Biggs\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0286225|name=John Forgeham}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Forgeham, John}}\n[[Category:1941 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]]\n[[Category:People from Kidderminster]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Worcestershire]]\n[[Category:20th-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:Accidental deaths from falls]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=November 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name                      = John Forgeham\n| image                     = \n| image_size                = \n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_name                = John Henry George Forgeham\n| birth_date                = 14 May 1941\n| birth_place               = [[Kidderminster]], Worcestershire, England\n| death_date                = {{death date and age|df=y|2017|3|10|1941|5|14}}\n| death_place               = [[Worthing]], West Sussex, England\n| nationality                 = British\n| occupation                = Actor\n| years_active              = 1963\u20132012\n| spouse                    = [[Georgina Hale]] (actress/divorced)<ref name=\"auto\">The People.co.uk</ref><br/>Fiesta mei Ling (actress/divorced)<ref name=\"auto\"/><br/>Arlene Garciano (2004\u20132006)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.co.uk/news/tm_objectid=16721296&method=full&siteid=93463&headline=exclusive--on-me-web-cam--son--name_page.html |title=Sunday People \u2013 News, views, gossip, pictures, video |publisher=People.co.uk |accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref>\n| children                  = 2\n}}\n\n'''John Henry George Forgeham''' (14 May 1941 \u2013 10 March 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/italian-job-john-forgeham-dead-10006919|title=The Italian Job and Footballers' Wives actor John Forgeham dies aged 75|last1=Das|first1=Shanti|last2=Saunders|first2=Emmeline|date=11 March 2017|newspaper=Daily Mirror|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>) was an English actor known for his television work, notably the role of businessman Frank Laslett in the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] series ''[[Footballers' Wives]]''.<ref>Footballers' Wives interview</ref>\n\nBorn in [[Kidderminster]], Worcestershire, Forgeham moved to [[Erdington]], Birmingham as a child,<ref name=guardian>[https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/mar/13/john-forgeham-obituary John Forgeham obituary] ''[[The Guardian]]'', 13 March 2017. Retrieved 13 March 2017.</ref> and trained at the [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]] (RADA) on a two-year scholarship (1962\u201364) and graduated with a RADA Silver medal for Best Performance student.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/john-forgeham-actor-dies-after-falling-out-of-bed-the-italian-job-footballers-wives-worthing-a7625036.html|title=Actor John Forgeham, who starred in The Italian Job, dies after falling out of bed|date=11 March 2017}}</ref> He was a member of the [[Royal Shakespeare Company]] (RSC) (from 1966 until 1972) and toured with the company both nationally and internationally. Whilst on tour in Australia he decided to stay longer than anticipated and founded the Globe Shakespeare Theatre in Sydney.<ref name=guardian/>\n\nHis many TV credits include: ''[[The Avengers (TV series)|The Avengers]]'', ''[[Z-Cars]]'', ''[[The Stone Tape]]'', ''[[Crossroads (UK TV series)|Crossroads]]'' (as [[Jim Baines]]) ''[[The Sweeney]]'', ''[[Ivanhoe (1982 film)|Ivanhoe]]'', ''[[Beau Geste (TV series)|Beau Geste]]'', ''[[Minder (TV series)|Minder]]'', ''[[The Professionals (TV series)|The Professionals]]'', ''[[Shoestring (TV series)|Shoestring]]'', ''[[Juliet Bravo]]'', ''[[C.A.T.S. Eyes]]'', ''[[Lovejoy]]'', ''[[Bergerac (TV series)|Bergerac]]'', ''[[The Governor (UK TV series)|The Governor]]'', ''Pulaski'', ''[[Making Out (TV series)|Making Out]]'', [[Nice Work (TV Drama)|''Nice Work'']], ''[[Prime Suspect]]'', ''[[London's Burning (TV series)|London's Burning]]'', ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'', ''[[The Bill]]'' and ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aveleyman.com/ActorCredit.aspx?ActorID=5898|title=John Forgeham|publisher=aveleyman.com}}</ref>\n\nFilm appearances include: ''[[The Italian Job]]'' (1969), ''[[Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall (film)|Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall]]'' (1973), ''[[Spy Story (film)|Spy Story]]'' (1976), ''[[Sheena (film)|Sheena]]'' (1984), ''[[Pope John Paul II (film)|Pope John Paul II]]'' (1984), ''The Laughter of God'' (1990), ''[[King of the Wind (film)|King of the Wind]]'' (1990), ''[[The Young Americans (film)|The Young Americans]]'' (1993), ''[[Staggered (film)|Staggered]]'' (1994), ''The Road to Ithaca'' (1999), ''[[Kiss of the Dragon]]'' (2001), [[Mean Machine (film)|''Mean Machine'']] (2001), ''[[Pledge of Allegiance (film)|Pledge of Allegiance]]'' (2007), ''[[Torture Room]]'' (2007) and ''[[Dead Man Running]]'' (2009).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2ba2927c21|title=John Forgeham}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004 he appeared in the second series of the ITV weight loss show, ''[[Celebrity Fit Club]].'' He replaced [[Freddie Starr]] as team captain, but was demoted five weeks later, the role being taken by [[James Whitaker (journalist)|James Whitaker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2b8a2a2002|title=Celebrity Fit Club[13/01/2004] (2004)}}</ref>\n\nForgeham died suddenly from [[internal bleeding]] after breaking a [[collarbone]] after falling out of bed at his home in [[Worthing]], West Sussex on 10 March 2017, aged 75.<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/john-forgeham-actor-dies-after-falling-out-of-bed-the-italian-job-footballers-wives-worthing-a7625036.html</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''The Partner'' (1963) \u2013 Adrian Marlowe\n*''[[The Italian Job]]'' (1969) \u2013 Frank\n*''[[Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall (film)|Adolf Hitler: My Part in His Downfall]]'' (1973) \u2013 Wally\n*''[[One Hour to Zero]]'' (1976) \u2013 Sam Rogers\n*''[[Spy Story (film)|Spy Story]]'' (1976) \u2013 Security Guard\n*''[[Star Wars (film)|Star Wars]]'' (1977) \u2013 Captain Bolvan (Imperial Officer) (uncredited)\n*''[[Pope John Paul II (film)|Pope John Paul II]]'' (1984) \u2013 Officer Moljek\n*''[[Sheena (film)|Sheena]]'' (1984) \u2013 Jorgensen\n*''[[The Inquiry (1986 film)|The Inquiry]]'' (1986) \u2013 Marco\n*''[[King of the Wind (film)|King of the Wind]]'' (1990) \u2013 Blacksmith\n*''[[The Young Americans (film)|The Young Americans]]'' (1993) \u2013 Detective Gray\n*''[[Staggered (film)|Staggered]]'' (1994) \u2013 Inspector Lubbock\n*''[[Remember Me? (film)|Remember Me?]]'' (1997) \u2013 Police inspector\n*''The Road to Ithaca'' (1999) \u2013 Kemal Ahmed\n*''[[Kiss of the Dragon]]'' (2001) \u2013 Max\n*''[[Mean Machine (film)|Mean Machine]]'' (2001) \u2013 Charlie Sykes\n*''[[Pledge of Allegiance (film)|Pledge of Allegiance]]'' (2007) \u2013 Mr. Green\n*''[[Dead Man Running]]'' (2009) \u2013 Terry Biggs\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0286225|name=John Forgeham}}\n\